# Language runtimes + dev-time tools, all managed by mise
# (https://mise.jdx.dev/). Run `mise install` to materialize them.
# mise itself comes from `brew install mise` (or the curl installer
# linked in CONTRIBUTING.md for non-Homebrew users).
#
# These get reflected via shims when you `eval "$(mise activate <shell>)"`,
# or you can prefix commands with `mise exec --` to run inside mise's
# environment without shell activation. The Makefile uses the latter.

python 3.11
go 1.22
bun 1.1.0
